CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE 2012 (14): DOMINICAN REPUBLIC
********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 23 Apr 2012
Source: Prensa Latina [edited]
http://www.plenglish.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=500042&Itemid=1


Dominican health authorities on Mon 23 Apr 2012 confirmed the death of 6 people due to cholera in Tamboril, province of Santiago, where the number of people affected amounts to 523.

Deputy minister of public health Yadira Perez reported that of all people affected by an outbreak of diarrhea, 36 tested positive for cholera. 19 patients with symptoms of cholera are currently hospitalized in the public hospital of Tamboril, 7 women and 12 men.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The last posting from Dominican Republic regarding cholera dated 20 Apr 2012, just 3 days prior to this one, mentions only one death and 6 confirmed cases. It appears that the outbreak in Santiago province has increased in this rainy season. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/2c36.]
